Poised to remain Nigeria’s leading musical band, Shuga Band led by Akin Shuga has concluded plans to host a live show at the Convention Centre, Eko Hotels and Suites, Victoria Island, Lagos on Sunday, October 21, 2018. The concert according to the band will be a memorable one, as guest will in a long time continue to relish the event with major performances to come from the professional band, creating a musical with loads of surprises. Speaking about the concert, Akin Shuga, who is overjoyed at how far the band has come, maintained that ‘Shuga Coated Concert’ would be nothing compared to anything ever witnessed from the band before. He said, “We are overjoyed at being able to remain consistent in a very dynamic event industry for 20 years. It is no small feat because we have seen many come and go. It is by the grace of God and the support of our friends all over the world who have continued to patronize us. “I am super excited because I can remember when this started. I know the struggles and the battles we fought personally and professionally to remain grounded and committed to excellence. Yes, today we are referred to as Nigeria’s most prestigious live band but we didn’t start like this; we have to pay our dues,” he added. Akin noted explained that the band with its cross cultural representation and performances in almost all geo-political zone in the country has not not only conquered Nigeria but gone ahead to headline multiple shows and events on the international scene. He added that the band has performed for notable personalities including presidents, governors, captain of industries and corporate bodies. On what the fans and guests should expect at the concert, Akin stated: “We have had hundreds of performances across Nigeria but what our friends who will attend the Shuga Coated Concert will experience will be nothing compared to anything they have seen from us before. “We are taking it 10 notches higher. This is a celebration of our fall and rise but more candidly, it is a celebration of those who have stood by us and made us their preferred for 20 years. I can assure you that we will deliver a world-class musical experience.” 